race.comment: DR. KATARINA (2) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing seventh (25.35) last time in a Grade 5 at this track. Should be very hard to beat this time. TERRORISING TOM (6) was in the minors two back (23.24) at Warragul but ran below best last time at this track, finishing 6th. Form here at the trip sound including three wins. The form from his last run stacks up well. Expected to run well. MALLY BOY (7) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at this track behind Rhine Star (25.27) in a Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Leading chance. LOCKED AND READY (1) can find the frame without surprising. Something for the Multiples: ECO BALE (5)
